Even though Florida's McKay voucher program was specifically created for students with disabilities, the law is structured in a way that penalizes middle- and low-income parents who cannot afford to pay tuition or fees that typically exceed the voucher's face value. Additionally, participating private schools are not required to offer special education services and even those that do offer these services are not required‰ÛÓunlike public schools‰ÛÓto monitor students' progress.147